Document_summary: This document is an Interconnection Agreement between Kauai Island Utility Cooperative and Kapaa Solar LLC regarding a Power Purchase Agreement for As-Available Energy. It includes details on Interconnection Agreements, Amendments to the PPA, and responsibilities of the Parties. The document outlines the terms and conditions for interconnecting the Small Generating Facility with the Cooperative's Transmission and/or Distribution System.

This document is an Interconnection Agreement between Kauai Island Utility Cooperative and Kapaa Solar LLC regarding the connection of a Small Generating Facility to the Cooperative's system. It outlines the terms, responsibilities, and procedures for interconnection. The Agreement covers aspects such as cost responsibility, termination, disputes, insurance, confidentiality, and more.

This document is an Interconnection Agreement between Kauai Island Utility Cooperative and Kapaa Solar LLC regarding the connection of a Small Generating Facility to the Cooperative's system. It outlines the terms, responsibilities, and procedures for interconnection, operation, and maintenance. The Agreement includes provisions for dispute resolution, insurance requirements, and compliance with laws and regulations.
